body:
#### System information

2.54.0 (but problem has existed probably from the start

OS & Version: Linux

Chain/Network: Polygon

#### Expected behaviour

Proxy Heimdall in nginx like this:

```
upstream polygon_heimdall_mainnet_full_proxy_1 {
  least_conn;
  #rpc origins
  server  127.0.0.1:1317;
}
```

```
location ^~ /polygon_heimdall_mainnet_full_1/ {
      auth_request /_validate_apikey;
      proxy_http_version 1.1;
      proxy_read_timeout 120s;
      proxy_send_timeout 120s;
      proxy_socket_keepalive on;
      proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;
      proxy_set_header Connection "upgrade";
      proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
      proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
      proxy_set_header Host $http_host;
      proxy_set_header X-NginX-Proxy true;
      proxy_pass    http://polygon_heimdall_mainnet_full_proxy_1/;

      # Error responses
      error_page 404 = @400;         # Treat invalid paths as bad requests
      #proxy_intercept_errors on;     # Do not send backend errors to client
      default_type application/json; # If no content-type, assume JSON
  }
```
  
and setting Erigon with 
```
--bor.heimdall='https://domain.com/polygon_heimdall_mainnet_full_1'
``` 
should work

#### Actual behaviour

Instead in the logs we can see that Erigon is ignoring any path after the domain:port

```
an error while trying fetching from Heimdall path=/milestone/lastNoAck attempt=1 error="error while fetching data from Heimdall: https://domain.com/milestone/lastNoAck:response code 404"
```

If I proxy like this:

```
location ^~ / {
      auth_request /_validate_apikey;
      proxy_http_version 1.1;
      proxy_read_timeout 120s;
      proxy_send_timeout 120s;
      proxy_socket_keepalive on;
      proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;
      proxy_set_header Connection "upgrade";
      proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
      proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
      proxy_set_header Host $http_host;
      proxy_set_header X-NginX-Proxy true;
      proxy_pass    http://polygon_heimdall_mainnet_full_proxy_1/;

      # Error responses
      error_page 404 = @400;         # Treat invalid paths as bad requests
      #proxy_intercept_errors on;     # Do not send backend errors to client
      default_type application/json; # If no content-type, assume JSON
  }
```
  
  It works fine because there is no path
  
  And yes, it is erigon because if I test the proxy like this:
  ```
curl https://domain.com/polygon_heimdall_mainnet_full_1/milestone/lastNoAck
``` 
it works just fine:
  Result:
  ```
{"height":"16652691","result":{"result":"6cefcdca-03a3-4efa-bc1b-b7740422b144 - 0x5b6e64bd8c65eb44b86bdce431d1f17308c3e1c6"}}
```
  
  @mh0lt
